Preconditions:
The input string `s` is not null.
The input string `s` is not empty.
The input array `queries` is not null.
The input array `queries` is not empty.
The length of the input string `s` is greater than or equal to the maximum value of the second element in any query in the input array `queries`.
The second element in each query in the input array `queries` is a valid index within the input string `s`.
The first element in each query in the input array `queries` is a non-negative integer.

Postconditions:
The returned array `answer` is not null.
The length of the returned array `answer` is equal to the length of the input array `queries`.
Each element in the returned array `answer` is either true or false.
The value of `answer[i]` is true if it is possible to make `s` a palindrome by performing operations specified by the `i-th` query.
The value of `answer[i]` is false if it is not possible to make `s` a palindrome by performing operations specified by the `i-th` query.